\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 CopperExport for iPhoto\
Version 0.2.1 - \cf2 Security fix, please see the "Server-side configuration" section\cf0 \

\f1\b0 February 24th, 2005.\
\
CopperExport for iPhoto is a plugin for iPhoto 4 and 5 which allows you to export pictures directly into a Coppermine gallery (http://coppermine.sf.net/).\
\
I would love to hear from you if you find it useful, or if you find something that does not work properly, or if you have any other comments or suggestions. See the email address at the bottom of this document.\
\
iPhoto 5 support has been incorporated, but I do not have iPhoto 5, so it has not been tested. Please drop me a line if you do.\
\
See the ChangeLog file for a detailed list of changes.\
\

\f0\b System Requirements
\f1\b0 \
\
CopperExport for iPhoto requires Mac OS X 10.3 Panther and iPhoto 4.x or 5.x.  iPhoto 2.x 
\f2\i may
\f1\i0  work, but has not been tested.  Versions of Mac OS X prior to 10.3 will certainly not work.\
\
It has been tested with Coppermine 1.3.2. Older versions may work, but have not been tested. See the notes below on optional (but recommended) server-side configuration.\
\

\f0\b Installation
\f1\b0 \
\
0. Quit iPhoto\
1. Locate the iPhoto application\
2. Open the Get Info window for iPhoto (File Menu -> Get Info)\
3. Disclose the "Plug-ins" section of the Get Info window.\
4. If you have a previous version of CopperExport installed, select it in the list and press "Remove..."\
5. Click "Add\'c9"\
6. Locate and select the folder "CopperExport.iPhotoExporter"\
