\f0\b \cf0 Server-side configuration\

\f3\i \
Please note: 
\f2\b0 if you had installed 
\f4\i0 xp_publish.php
\f2\i  from CopperExport 0.1, please replace it with the new version to support setting the description when creating a new album.\

\f3\b \cf2 IMPORTANT: 
\f2\b0 The version of xp_publish.php distributed with CopperExport 0.2 and prior contained a bad security vulnerability. Please update to the new version!
\f1\i0 \cf0 \

\f0\b \

\f1\b0 CopperExport uses the existing "Windows XP export wizard" interface in Coppermine. Unfortunately, in the default distribution of Coppermine, this interface does not accept additional information like the title, description and keywords for a picture, or the description for new albums. If you have access to your Coppermine installation directory, you can make some small changes (4 lines) to enable this functionality.\
\

\f2\i If you cannot do not have the possibility of making these changes, you can still upload files, but the caption, description and keywords will not be applied, or the description for new albums.\

\f1\i0 \
Included in this release are two files:\
\
